    "recap_headline": "Akron Athletics",
    "recap_text": "YPSILANTI, Mich. -\nThe Akron Zips fell 9-8 in a 10-inning matchup to the Eastern Michigan Eagles Saturday.\nIn the batter's box, the Zips were led by\nBlake Bowen\n, who went 3-for-5 on the day with a double, a walk and an RBI.\nHenry Hayman\nput together a noteworthy day at the plate as well, going 2-for-4 with a double and an RBI.\nRyan Jones\nalso contributed for Akron,\u00a0adding three walks and an RBI.\nGarrett Groce\n(0-2) took the loss on the mound for Akron.\nTaylor Bednar\nwas a bright spot out of the bullpen, going 2.1 innings, surrendering two runs, zero earned, on two hits, walking four and striking out four.\nElijah Griffith\ngot the start for the Blue and Gold, going six innings while allowing three runs, all earned, on nine hits and striking out five.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Zips were trailing 3-0 in the fifth inning when they first put runs on the board. Akron's offense started clicking and put up seven runs, including a one-run walk off the bat of Jones.\nThe Eagles then gained ground, narrowing the lead to 7-6 until the Zips expanded their advantage in the ninth. Akron pushed across a run on\nGabe Mathison's\ntwo-out RBI double, which brought the Zips lead to 8-6. The Zips were unable to hold the lead, as Eastern Michigan scored three times over the remaining one inning to grab the 9-8 win.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Bowen led the Zips, picking up three base hits in the ballgame.\n\u00bb Every Zips starter reached base safely in the loss.\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the fifth, when it pushed seven runs across.\n\u00bb Akron left 16 runners stranded on base in the loss.\n\u00bb The Zips got three hits in eight at-bats with the bases loaded.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 55 Eastern Michigan hitters in the game, allowing 12 ground balls and seven fly balls while striking out 10.\n\u00bb The Zips drew eight walks from Eastern Michigan pitching.\n\u00bb Bowen led the Zips at the plate, going 3 for 5 with a double and an RBI.\nW